      "content": "Our current routing system is based on a combination of historical routing data, driver experience, and traffic volume. Reviewing the report, I noticed that this \"systemic bias\" is likely due to an unintended consequence of optimizing for driver retention and efficiency. However, upon closer inspection, I found that individual driver accounts from the problematic routes have a higher average tenure and lower turnover rates, suggesting that our metrics may have unintentionally prioritized current drivers over others from marginalized groups. This may indicate a form of implicit bias in our system.",
